{
  "name": "Bullseye Training",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/magic/symbols/runes-star-orange.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Category: Bukijutsu </p><p>You have trained under the teachings of the land of Bows either directly or by descension, gaining the following benefits: </p><p>• Increase your Strength or Dexterity score by 1, to a maximum of 20.</p><p>• You gain proficiency in one set of equipment as these weapons become known as Bullseye Weapons.</p><p>  - Short Bows, Long Bows &amp; Heavy Jacket </p><p>  - Light Crossbows, Heavy Crossbows &amp; Heavy Jacket </p><p>• Weapon attacks from a Bullseye Weapon ignores structures and constructs that would intercept the damage dealt, dealing damage directly to the target creature(s).</p><p>• You cannot be disarmed of your Bullseye Weapon and they cannot be broken while you are wielding them.</p><p>• When you take the attack action using a Bullseye weapon you can knock 2 shots instead of one.</p><p> For the remainder of this turn, ranged weapon attacks you make with your Bullseye Weapon doubles its weapon damage die.</p><p> Reduce your ammunition die by one step, instead of rolling.</p><p></p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
